com.hcl.domino.data

Interface DocumentProperties


  • public interface DocumentProperties
    Interface to define Document Properties as a serializable object, avoiding dependencies on the underlying Document and Items. This allows quick programmatic access to summary details about a Document. A common requirement for this is to display as a Properties window for developers (as found in Notes Client). A strong use case for having it available as an object is to compare two documents, most typically a main document and its conflict. Another strong use case would be to store all or a subset for audit tracking purposes.
    Since:
    0.5.0
    Author:
    Paul Withers
